{"kind":"blogger#post","id":"7585637410696355935","blog":{"id":"2360593805083673688"},"published":"2012-11-08T06:00:00-08:00","updated":"2012-11-14T08:43:48-08:00","url":"http://www.quietlikehorses.com/2012/11/snack-of-day-fruit-flavored-mochi.html","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/7585637410696355935","title":"Snack of the Day: Fruit-Flavored Mochi ","content":"<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">\n</div>\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\">\n<a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-QfCvAF7SAXk/UJtfycMDZPI/AAAAAAAAQmo/Es4_KhJwNUk/s1600/snack+of+the+day+mochi.png\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img alt=\"fruit mochi\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-QfCvAF7SAXk/UJtfycMDZPI/AAAAAAAAQmo/Es4_KhJwNUk/s1600/snack+of+the+day+mochi.png\" title=\"fruit mochi\" /></a></div>\n<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: left;\">\nDo you ever go to the Japanese grocery store? Walking through one is a great practice in self-control because I always want every snack in sight. Everything is so cute! On our last visit to <a href=\"http://bit.ly/SOsSIf\" target=\"_blank\">Mitsuwa</a>, I bought fruit-flavored mochi for an afternoon snack. They're just slightly sweet with a wonderfully soft, doughy, chewy texture. It's what I like to imagine big fluffy clouds would taste like.&nbsp;</div>\n","author":{"id":"06629562195146939698","displayName":"Sobrina Tung","url":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/06629562195146939698","image":{"url":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TI8X4CO5nWI/AAAAAAAAERk/4p5D74gYdFE/S45/me.JPG"}},"replies":{"totalItems":"0","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/7585637410696355935/comments"},"labels":["Snack of the Day","To Eat"]}